{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":227079,"duration_api_ms":222596,"num_turns":2,"result":"## core_business_v2/ingestion Module Architecture\n\n### Overview\n\nThe ingestion module is an **event-driven entity processing pipeline** built on Spring Boot + Redis Streams. It receives network entity data (hosts, users, adapters), deduplicates via fingerprinting, and processes each entity through a 4-stage state machine.\n\n---\n\n### REST Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/ingestion/events` | Main entry — ingests an entity event, returns async result |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/ingestion/health-check` | Health probe |\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/entities/query` | Query entities by stage/code with pagination |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/entities/{id}` | Get entity by ID |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/entities/{id}/display-status` | Human-readable processing status |\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/fingerprint/calculate` | Calculate attribute fingerprint (MD5) |\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/policy/apply-existing-entities` | Mark all entities for policy re-evaluation |\n\n---\n\n### Request Processing Flow\n\n```\nREST POST /ingestion/events\n  → IngestionController: generate requestId, register CompletableFuture, publish to Redis Stream\n    → IngestionInternalConsumer: deserialize, call orchestrator\n      → IngestionOrchestrator (3-tier lookup):\n          1. Redis cache hit? → CachedExistingEntityHandler\n          2. Acquire create-lock → DB lookup → DbExistingEntityHandler\n          3. No DB match → NewEntityHandler\n```\n\n**For existing entities**, the orchestrator computes a fingerprint and selects one of 4 handlers via `FingerprintHandlerRegistry`:\n\n| Fingerprint | Lock Acquired | Handler | Action |\n|-------------|--------------|---------|--------|\n| Same | Yes | SameAttributesWithLockAcquiredHandler | No-op, return entity |\n| Same | No | SameAttributesWithLockNotAcquiredHandler | Spin-wait for current processing to finish |\n| Different | Yes | DifferentAttributesWithLockAcquiredHandler | Reset to PENDING, restart state machine |\n| Different | No | DifferentAttributesWithLockNotAcquiredHandler | **Request merge**: interrupt running SM, acquire lock, restart |\n\nA special `DeviceTypeChangedHandler` handles type escalation (HOST → USER_HOST_BINDING).\n\n---\n\n### State Machine (`EntityStateMachine`)\n\n4 stages, executed sequentially in a loop:\n\n```\nPENDING → LabelService.label() → LABELED\nLABELED → PolicyService.evaluate() → EVALUATED\nEVALUATED → EnforcementService.enforce() → ENFORCED (terminal)\n```\n\nKey design decisions:\n- **Each stage persists independently** via `@Transactional(REQUIRES_NEW)` — crash recovery resumes from last saved stage\n- **Per-stage retry**: up to 3 attempts with exponential backoff + jitter\n- **Interruptible**: checks `entity.interrupted` before each stage (for request merge)\n- **Failpoint injection**: chaos testing hooks before/after each service call\n- Tracks `ingestion_state_machine_seconds{result, finalStage}` metrics\n\n---\n\n### Key Classes by Layer\n\n**Controllers**: `IngestionController`, `EntityController`, `FingerprintController`, `PolicyController`\n\n**Consumer/Orchestration**: `IngestionInternalConsumer`, `IngestionExternalConsumer`, `IngestionOrchestrator`\n\n**Handlers** (strategy pattern): 4 fingerprint handlers + `NewEntityHandler` + `DeviceTypeChangedHandler`\n\n**State Machine**: `EntityStateMachine`, `EntityStageTransactionRunner`\n\n**Stage Services**: `LabelService` (rule engine), `PolicyService` (evaluation), `EnforcementService` (actions)\n\n**Domain**: `Entity` (main JPA entity with processing state), `HostRecord`, `UserRecord`, `DynamicClient`\n\n**Infrastructure**: `EntityCache` (Redis), `RedisDelayQueueUtil` (exponential backoff requeue), `IngestionCallbackRegistry` (async REST → future), `EntityProcessingRegistry` (active processing tracker)\n\n**Recovery**: `EntityRecoveryService`, `StuckEntityRecoveryJob`, `PolicyReprocessJob`\n\n---\n\n### Concurrency Model\n\n- **Redis distributed locks**: create-lock (10s TTL) prevents duplicate entity creation; process-lock (30s TTL) serializes state machine execution per entity\n- **Lock contention** → delay queue with exponential backoff (2s → 32s)\n- **Request merge**: when a new request arrives with different attributes while the entity is mid-processing, the running state machine is interrupted and restarted with merged context\n- **Async REST**: controller registers a `CompletableFuture`, returns `Mono`; consumer completes the future when processing finishes (configurable 60s timeout)","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"ff8f1396-bac1-45f1-98f5-6309e8c22bc7","total_cost_usd":0.5484863,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":23653,"cache_read_input_tokens":36936,"output_tokens":1526,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":23653,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6[1m]":{"inputTokens":4,"outputTokens":1526,"cacheReadInputTokens":36936,"cacheCreationInputTokens":23653,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.20446925,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":1610,"outputTokens":20961,"cacheReadInputTokens":1018483,"cacheCreationInputTokens":108603,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.34401705,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"cc119869-714e-42c8-8a91-e6c44e2de3fb"}
